Note: ===================================================================
Note: HIR TO MATLAB GENERATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Reconstructs MATLAB source code from the canonical typed HIR
Note: (hir_nodes.runa) produced by matlab_to_hir.runa, for the Translation
Note: universal translation system.

Note: This backend is the consumer half of the model-1 typed-HIR contract:
Note: it reads real HIR_* nodes via hir_get_* accessors and re-emits MATLAB.
Note: MATLAB-specific details that have no HIR node kind (matrix vs
Note: element-wise operators, the power operator, transpose, ranges, cell
Note: arrays, function handles, anonymous functions, parfor/spmd, switch,
Note: try/catch, global/persistent, multiple return values) are carried as
Note: metadata that matlab_to_hir attached; the two files agree on those
Note: exact keys.

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/matlab/hir_to_matlab.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore

Note: ===================================================================
Note: GENERATION CONTEXT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The context threads the indentation level and the line buffer through the
recursive emission. Identity (not copying) carries the mutation across the
recursion: every emitter appends to the same code_buffer and adjusts the
same indent_level.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabGenerationContext":
    indent_level as Integer
    code_buffer as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
The factory zero-initialises the indent level and allocates the line buffer
so the first emit cannot inherit stale state from a previous translation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_generation_context" returns Integer:
    Let ctx be a value of type MatlabGenerationContext with
        indent_level as 0,
        code_buffer as proc list_create from ListCore

    Return ctx
End Process

@Reasoning:
Indentation is a counter; the whitespace is materialised only when a line is
emitted. Increase/decrease are symmetric and every block open has a matching
close in the same routine.
@End Reasoning
Process called "increase_indent" takes ctx as Integer:
    Set ctx.indent_level to ctx.indent_level plus 1
End Process

Process called "decrease_indent" takes ctx as Integer:
    Set ctx.indent_level to ctx.indent_level minus 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds the current indent string by repeating MATLAB's 4-space unit
indent_level times. Constructed per line because the indent is small and the
arena allocator amortises the cost.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_current_indent" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let indent be ""
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ctx.indent_level:
        Set indent to proc string_concat from StringPrim with indent, "    "
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return indent
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single point through which all MATLAB lines reach the buffer so no emitter
forgets the indent prefix.
@End Reasoning
Process called "emit_line" takes ctx as Integer, line as Integer:
    Let indent be proc get_current_indent with ctx
    Let full_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with indent, line
    proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.code_buffer, full_line
End Process

@Reasoning:
Blank lines bypass indentation so they are truly empty per MATLAB style.
@End Reasoning
Process called "emit_blank_line" takes ctx as Integer:
    proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.code_buffer, ""
End Process

@Reasoning:
Joins the buffered lines with newline separators (no trailing newline) so
the output is byte-stable for golden comparisons.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_generated_code" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let result be ""
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with ctx.code_buffer
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let line be proc list_get from ListCore with ctx.code_buffer, i
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, line
        Let last_index be count minus 1
        If i is less than last_index:
            Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, "\n"
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return result
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: METADATA HELPERS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
A flag is present when hir_get_metadata returns a non-zero handle whose
string value equals "1". Centralising the test keeps every emitter's flag
check identical.
@End Reasoning
Process called "metadata_flag" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value be proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with node, key
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let is_set be proc string_equals from StringCore with value, "1"
    Return is_set
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the raw string value stored under a metadata key, or 0 when absent.
Used for non-flag metadata (operator spellings, joined name lists).
@End Reasoning
Process called "metadata_value" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc hir_get_metadata from HIR with node, key
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN GENERATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Owns the context lifecycle: a fresh context per call so concurrent
translations never share mutable state. The module is walked, then the
buffered lines are joined into the final source string.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_matlab_from_hir" takes hir_module as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ctx be proc create_generation_context
    proc generate_module with ctx, hir_module
    Let matlab_code be proc get_generated_code with ctx
    Return matlab_code
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MODULE GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
MATLAB has no modules. Each top-level declaration is emitted in order:
classes via generate_class, functions via generate_function (the synthetic
matlab_script_main function's body holds hoisted script statements and is
emitted as an ordinary function). A blank line separates declarations.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_module" takes ctx as Integer, hir_module as Integer:
    If hir_module is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let declarations be proc hir_get_declarations from HIR with hir_module
    Let decl_count be proc list_length from ListCore with declarations
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than decl_count:
        Let decl be proc list_get from ListCore with declarations, i
        Let decl_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with decl

        If decl_type is equal to HIR.HIR_CLASS:
            proc generate_class with ctx, decl
            proc emit_blank_line with ctx
        End If

        If decl_type is equal to HIR.HIR_FUNCTION:
            Let func_name be proc hir_get_function_name from HIR with decl
            Let is_script_main be proc string_equals from StringCore with func_name, "matlab_script_main"
            If is_script_main is equal to 1:
                proc generate_script_body with ctx, decl
            Otherwise:
                proc generate_function with ctx, decl
            End If
            proc emit_blank_line with ctx
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
The synthetic script wrapper has no MATLAB syntactic form; its body
statements are emitted directly at top level, reproducing a MATLAB script
file.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_script_body" takes ctx as Integer, func_node as Integer:
    Let body be proc hir_get_function_body from HIR with func_node
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_block_inner with ctx, body
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CLASS GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
MATLAB classdef requires members partitioned into properties / methods
blocks each with their own end. Members are bucketed by HIR kind (field vs
method) and emitted contiguously. Base class, events and the enumeration
flag are reconstructed from the class metadata the frontend attached.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_class" takes ctx as Integer, class_node as Integer:
    Let class_name be proc hir_get_class_name from HIR with class_node
    Let class_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "classdef ", class_name

    Let base_class be proc metadata_value with class_node, "matlab_base_class"
    If base_class is not equal to 0:
        Set class_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with class_line, " < "
        Set class_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with class_line, base_class
    End If

    proc emit_line with ctx, class_line
    proc increase_indent with ctx

    Let members be proc hir_get_class_members from HIR with class_node
    Let member_count be proc list_length from ListCore with members

    Let is_enum be proc metadata_flag with class_node, "matlab_enumeration"

    Note: Properties / enumeration values
    Let field_count be 0
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than member_count:
        Let m be proc list_get from ListCore with members, k
        Let mt be proc hir_node_type from HIR with m
        If mt is equal to HIR.HIR_FIELD:
            Set field_count to field_count plus 1
        End If
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While

    If field_count is greater than 0:
        proc emit_blank_line with ctx
        If is_enum is equal to 1:
            proc emit_line with ctx, "enumeration"
        Otherwise:
            proc emit_line with ctx, "properties"
        End If
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than member_count:
            Let member be proc list_get from ListCore with members, i
            Let member_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with member
            If member_type is equal to HIR.HIR_FIELD:
                Let field_name be proc hir_get_field_name from HIR with member
                proc emit_line with ctx, field_name
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc decrease_indent with ctx
        proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
    End If

    Note: Methods
    Let method_present be 0
    Let p be 0
    While p is less than member_count:
        Let mm be proc list_get from ListCore with members, p
        Let mmt be proc hir_node_type from HIR with mm
        Let is_func be 0
        If mmt is equal to HIR.HIR_FUNCTION:
            Set is_func to 1
        End If
        If mmt is equal to HIR.HIR_METHOD:
            Set is_func to 1
        End If
        If is_func is equal to 1:
            Set method_present to 1
        End If
        Set p to p plus 1
    End While

    If method_present is equal to 1:
        proc emit_blank_line with ctx
        proc emit_line with ctx, "methods"
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than member_count:
            Let mem be proc list_get from ListCore with members, j
            Let memt be proc hir_node_type from HIR with mem
            Let emit_it be 0
            If memt is equal to HIR.HIR_FUNCTION:
                Set emit_it to 1
            End If
            If memt is equal to HIR.HIR_METHOD:
                Set emit_it to 1
            End If
            If emit_it is equal to 1:
                proc emit_blank_line with ctx
                proc generate_function with ctx, mem
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc decrease_indent with ctx
        proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
    End If

    Note: Events
    Let events be proc metadata_value with class_node, "matlab_events"
    If events is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_blank_line with ctx
        proc emit_line with ctx, "events"
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        Let event_names be proc split_on_comma_space with events
        Let ev_count be proc list_length from ListCore with event_names
        Let e be 0
        While e is less than ev_count:
            Let ev be proc list_get from ListCore with event_names, e
            proc emit_line with ctx, ev
            Set e to e plus 1
        End While
        proc decrease_indent with ctx
        proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
    End If

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Reconstructs the MATLAB function header. Multiple outputs are read from the
"matlab_output_params" metadata to rebuild "[a, b] = name(...)"; a single
output uses "matlab_single_output" for "y = name(...)"; absent both yields a
no-output "name(...)". Input parameters come from the real HIR parameter
list. The body block is emitted at the next indent level, closed by 'end'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_function" takes ctx as Integer, func_node as Integer:
    Let func_line be "function "

    Let output_params be proc metadata_value with func_node, "matlab_output_params"
    Let single_output be proc metadata_value with func_node, "matlab_single_output"

    If output_params is not equal to 0:
        Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, "["
        Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, output_params
        Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, "] = "
    Otherwise:
        If single_output is not equal to 0:
            Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, single_output
            Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, " = "
        End If
    End If

    Let func_name be proc hir_get_function_name from HIR with func_node
    Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, func_name
    Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, "("

    Let params_handle be proc hir_get_parameters from HIR with func_node
    Let params be proc hir_get_parameter_list from HIR with params_handle
    Let param_count be proc list_length from ListCore with params
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param be proc list_get from ListCore with params, i
        Let param_name be proc hir_get_parameter_name from HIR with param
        Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, param_name
        Let last be param_count minus 1
        If i is less than last:
            Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Set func_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_line, ")"
    proc emit_line with ctx, func_line

    proc increase_indent with ctx
    Let body be proc hir_get_function_body from HIR with func_node
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_block_inner with ctx, body
    End If
    proc decrease_indent with ctx

    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Statement dispatcher. Blocks carry MATLAB-specific framing via metadata
(spmd, try, global/persistent); assignment expression statements emit
"lhs = rhs;"; control flow maps onto MATLAB if/for/while/switch; jumps emit
their keyword; a plain expression statement emits "expr;".
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_node as Integer:
    If stmt_node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let stmt_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with stmt_node

    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_BLOCK:
        proc generate_block_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_IF:
        proc generate_if_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_WHILE:
        proc generate_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_FOR_IN:
        proc generate_for_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_RETURN:
        proc emit_line with ctx, "return"
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_BREAK:
        proc emit_line with ctx, "break"
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_CONTINUE:
        proc emit_line with ctx, "continue"
        Return
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to HIR.HIR_EXPR_STMT:
        proc generate_expression_statement with ctx, stmt_node
        Return
    End If

    Note: A bare expression node used as a statement.
    Let expr_str be proc generate_expression with ctx, stmt_node
    Let stmt_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with expr_str, ";"
    proc emit_line with ctx, stmt_line
End Process

@Reasoning:
An expression statement holding a simple-assignment expression renders as
"lhs = rhs;" (MATLAB has no let-declaration); any other expression renders
as "expr;". The trailing ';' suppresses MATLAB's automatic echo.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_expression_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_node as Integer:
    Let expr be proc hir_get_expression_statement_expr from HIR with stmt_node
    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let expr_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with expr
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR:
        Let lhs be proc hir_get_assign_lhs from HIR with expr
        Let rhs be proc hir_get_assign_rhs from HIR with expr
        Let lhs_str be proc generate_expression with ctx, lhs
        Let rhs_str be proc generate_expression with ctx, rhs
        Let assign_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with lhs_str, " = "
        Set assign_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with assign_line, rhs_str
        Set assign_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with assign_line, ";"
        proc emit_line with ctx, assign_line
        Return
    End If

    Let expr_str be proc generate_expression with ctx, expr
    Let line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with expr_str, ";"
    proc emit_line with ctx, line
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits the statements of an HIR block inside the caller's indent context,
without any opening/closing keyword. Used for function/script/branch bodies.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_block_inner" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Let statements be proc hir_get_block_statements from HIR with block_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with statements
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with statements, i
        proc generate_statement with ctx, stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
A block reaching the statement dispatcher (rather than a body context) may
carry MATLAB framing metadata. A spmd block is wrapped in "spmd ... end"; a
global/persistent block re-emits the original "global a b c" line from its
"matlab_decl_names" metadata; a try block re-emits the try/catch frame; an
ordinary block flattens into the parent scope (MATLAB has no anonymous
block).
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_block_statement" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Let decl_names be proc metadata_value with block_node, "matlab_decl_names"
    Let is_global be proc metadata_flag with block_node, "matlab_global"
    Let is_persistent be proc metadata_flag with block_node, "matlab_persistent"

    If is_global is equal to 1:
        Let global_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "global ", decl_names
        proc emit_line with ctx, global_line
        Return
    End If
    If is_persistent is equal to 1:
        Let persistent_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "persistent ", decl_names
        proc emit_line with ctx, persistent_line
        Return
    End If

    Let is_spmd be proc metadata_flag with block_node, "matlab_spmd"
    If is_spmd is equal to 1:
        proc emit_line with ctx, "spmd"
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        proc generate_block_inner with ctx, block_node
        proc decrease_indent with ctx
        proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
        Return
    End If

    Let is_try be proc metadata_flag with block_node, "matlab_try"
    If is_try is equal to 1:
        proc generate_try_block with ctx, block_node
        Return
    End If

    proc generate_block_inner with ctx, block_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A try-block carries its statements as: a "try" string marker, the try body
block, then optionally a "catch" marker and the catch body block. The
markers let the flat representation re-emit MATLAB's try / catch (var)? /
end frame, with the optional exception variable from
"matlab_catch_var" metadata.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_try_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Let catch_var be proc metadata_value with block_node, "matlab_catch_var"

    Let statements be proc hir_get_block_statements from HIR with block_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with statements

    proc emit_line with ctx, "try"
    proc increase_indent with ctx

    Note: statements layout: try-marker, try-body, [catch-marker, catch-body]
    Let in_catch be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with statements, i
        Let marker_text be proc extract_string_marker with stmt
        Let is_try_marker be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker_text, "try"
        Let is_catch_marker be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker_text, "catch"

        If is_try_marker is equal to 1:
            Note: skip; frame already opened
        Otherwise:
            If is_catch_marker is equal to 1:
                proc decrease_indent with ctx
                Let catch_line be "catch"
                If catch_var is not equal to 0:
                    Set catch_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with "catch ", catch_var
                End If
                proc emit_line with ctx, catch_line
                proc increase_indent with ctx
                Set in_catch to 1
            Otherwise:
                proc generate_statement with ctx, stmt
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the literal text of an expression statement that wraps a string
literal (the try/catch frame markers), or the empty string for any other
statement. Lets generate_try_block recognise its frame markers structurally.
@End Reasoning
Process called "extract_string_marker" takes stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    End If
    Let stmt_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with stmt
    If stmt_type is not equal to HIR.HIR_EXPR_STMT:
        Return ""
    End If
    Let expr be proc hir_get_expression_statement_expr from HIR with stmt
    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    End If
    Let expr_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with expr
    If expr_type is not equal to HIR.HIR_STRING_LITERAL:
        Return ""
    End If
    Return proc hir_get_string_literal_value from HIR with expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
The HIR if-chain (with nested ifs in else slots) is re-emitted as MATLAB
if / elseif / else / end. A "matlab_switch" flag on the head node selects
switch re-emission instead, recovering the original switch/case form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_if_statement" takes ctx as Integer, if_node as Integer:
    Let is_switch be proc metadata_flag with if_node, "matlab_switch"
    If is_switch is equal to 1:
        proc generate_switch_statement with ctx, if_node
        Return
    End If

    Let condition be proc hir_get_if_condition from HIR with if_node
    Let then_block be proc hir_get_if_then from HIR with if_node
    Let cond_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, condition
    Let if_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "if ", cond_expr
    proc emit_line with ctx, if_line

    proc increase_indent with ctx
    proc generate_statement with ctx, then_block
    proc decrease_indent with ctx

    proc generate_if_tail with ctx, if_node

    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks the else chain. When the else slot holds a nested HIR if, it is
re-emitted as MATLAB 'elseif cond' and recursion continues down its else;
otherwise the else slot is an ordinary block re-emitted as 'else'. This
flattens the nested HIR back into MATLAB's flat elseif/else form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_if_tail" takes ctx as Integer, if_node as Integer:
    Let else_block be proc hir_get_if_else from HIR with if_node
    If else_block is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let else_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with else_block
    If else_type is equal to HIR.HIR_IF:
        Let condition be proc hir_get_if_condition from HIR with else_block
        Let then_block be proc hir_get_if_then from HIR with else_block
        Let cond_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, condition
        Let elseif_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "elseif ", cond_expr
        proc emit_line with ctx, elseif_line

        proc increase_indent with ctx
        proc generate_statement with ctx, then_block
        proc decrease_indent with ctx

        proc generate_if_tail with ctx, else_block
    Otherwise:
        proc emit_line with ctx, "else"
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        proc generate_statement with ctx, else_block
        proc decrease_indent with ctx
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Re-emits the switch form from the if-chain the frontend built. The head if's
condition is "scrut == case_val"; its left operand is the scrutinee
(emitted once after 'switch') and the right operand is the first case value.
Each nested if in the else slot contributes another 'case value'; a
non-if else block is the 'otherwise' body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_switch_statement" takes ctx as Integer, head_if as Integer:
    Let head_cond be proc hir_get_if_condition from HIR with head_if
    Let scrutinee be proc hir_get_binary_left from HIR with head_cond
    Let scrut_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, scrutinee
    Let switch_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "switch ", scrut_expr
    proc emit_line with ctx, switch_line
    proc increase_indent with ctx

    Let current be head_if
    Let walking be 1
    While walking is equal to 1:
        Let cond be proc hir_get_if_condition from HIR with current
        Let case_val be proc hir_get_binary_right from HIR with cond
        Let case_val_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, case_val
        Let case_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "case ", case_val_expr
        proc emit_line with ctx, case_line

        Let case_body be proc hir_get_if_then from HIR with current
        proc increase_indent with ctx
        proc generate_statement with ctx, case_body
        proc decrease_indent with ctx

        Let else_slot be proc hir_get_if_else from HIR with current
        If else_slot is equal to 0:
            Set walking to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let else_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with else_slot
            If else_type is equal to HIR.HIR_IF:
                Set current to else_slot
            Otherwise:
                proc emit_line with ctx, "otherwise"
                proc increase_indent with ctx
                proc generate_statement with ctx, else_slot
                proc decrease_indent with ctx
                Set walking to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc decrease_indent with ctx
    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

@Reasoning:
"while cond ... end" emitted directly from the HIR while node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, while_node as Integer:
    Let condition be proc hir_get_while_condition from HIR with while_node
    Let body be proc hir_get_while_body from HIR with while_node
    Let cond_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, condition
    Let while_line be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "while ", cond_expr
    proc emit_line with ctx, while_line

    proc increase_indent with ctx
    proc generate_statement with ctx, body
    proc decrease_indent with ctx

    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

@Reasoning:
"for var = iter ... end" emitted from the HIR for-in node; the
"matlab_parfor" flag selects the parfor keyword.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_for_statement" takes ctx as Integer, for_node as Integer:
    Let var_name be proc hir_get_for_in_variable from HIR with for_node
    Let iterable be proc hir_get_for_in_iterable from HIR with for_node
    Let body be proc hir_get_for_in_body from HIR with for_node

    Let iter_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, iterable

    Let is_parfor be proc metadata_flag with for_node, "matlab_parfor"
    Let for_line be ""
    If is_parfor is equal to 1:
        Set for_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with "parfor ", var_name
    Otherwise:
        Set for_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with "for ", var_name
    End If
    Set for_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with for_line, " = "
    Set for_line to proc string_concat from StringPrim with for_line, iter_expr
    proc emit_line with ctx, for_line

    proc increase_indent with ctx
    proc generate_statement with ctx, body
    proc decrease_indent with ctx

    proc emit_line with ctx, "end"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION GENERATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Expression dispatcher returning a string. Literals, identifiers, list
literals (matrix/cell), binary/unary operators, calls (including lambda and
range encodings), index and member access are reconstructed. Unknown shapes
return "unknown_expr" rather than aborting, preserving stability.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr_node is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    End If

    Let expr_type be proc hir_node_type from HIR with expr_node

    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_INT_LITERAL:
        Return proc hir_get_int_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL:
        Return proc hir_get_float_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_STRING_LITERAL:
        Let value be proc hir_get_string_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
        Let quoted be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "'", value
        Set quoted to proc string_concat from StringPrim with quoted, "'"
        Return quoted
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_BOOL_LITERAL:
        Let bool_value be proc hir_get_bool_literal_value from HIR with expr_node
        If bool_value is equal to 1:
            Return "true"
        End If
        Return "false"
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Return proc generate_identifier with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_LIST_LITERAL:
        Return proc generate_list_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_BINARY_EXPR:
        Return proc generate_binary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_UNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc generate_unary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_CALL_EXPR:
        Return proc generate_call_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_INDEX_EXPR:
        Return proc generate_index_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_MEMBER_EXPR:
        Return proc generate_member_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to HIR.HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR:
        Let lhs be proc hir_get_assign_lhs from HIR with expr_node
        Let rhs be proc hir_get_assign_rhs from HIR with expr_node
        Let lhs_str be proc generate_expression with ctx, lhs
        Let rhs_str be proc generate_expression with ctx, rhs
        Let assign be proc string_concat from StringPrim with lhs_str, " = "
        Set assign to proc string_concat from StringPrim with assign, rhs_str
        Return assign
    End If

    Return "unknown_expr"
End Process

@Reasoning:
An identifier carrying "matlab_func_handle" re-prepends '@'; one carrying
"matlab_colon_all" is the bare ':'; otherwise the plain name is returned.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_identifier" takes ctx as Integer, id_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_colon_all be proc metadata_flag with id_node, "matlab_colon_all"
    If is_colon_all is equal to 1:
        Return ":"
    End If

    Let name be proc hir_get_identifier_name from HIR with id_node
    Let is_handle be proc metadata_flag with id_node, "matlab_func_handle"
    If is_handle is equal to 1:
        Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with "@", name
    End If
    Return name
End Process

@Reasoning:
A list literal flagged "matlab_cell" re-emits "{a, b}"; otherwise it is a
matrix re-emitted as "[...]" with rows re-split using the per-row element
counts stored in "matlab_matrix_rows" (semicolon-separated counts). Within a
row, elements are space-separated and rows are joined with "; ".
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_list_literal" takes ctx as Integer, list_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let elements be proc hir_get_list_elements from HIR with list_node
    Let elem_count be proc list_length from ListCore with elements

    Let is_cell be proc metadata_flag with list_node, "matlab_cell"
    If is_cell is equal to 1:
        Let cell_result be "{"
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than elem_count:
            Let elem be proc list_get from ListCore with elements, i
            Let elem_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, elem
            Set cell_result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with cell_result, elem_expr
            Let last be elem_count minus 1
            If i is less than last:
                Set cell_result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with cell_result, ", "
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Set cell_result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with cell_result, "}"
        Return cell_result
    End If

    Note: Matrix: rebuild rows from "matlab_matrix_rows" element counts.
    Let rows_meta be proc metadata_value with list_node, "matlab_matrix_rows"
    Let result be "["
    If rows_meta is equal to 0:
        Note: No row metadata - emit a single row.
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than elem_count:
            Let elem2 be proc list_get from ListCore with elements, j
            Let elem2_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, elem2
            Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, elem2_expr
            Let last2 be elem_count minus 1
            If j is less than last2:
                Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, " "
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Let row_counts be proc split_on_semicolon with rows_meta
        Let row_total be proc list_length from ListCore with row_counts
        Let elem_index be 0
        Let r be 0
        While r is less than row_total:
            Let count_text be proc list_get from ListCore with row_counts, r
            Let row_len be proc parse_decimal with count_text
            If r is greater than 0:
                Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, "; "
            End If
            Let c be 0
            While c is less than row_len:
                Let cell_elem be proc list_get from ListCore with elements, elem_index
                Let cell_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, cell_elem
                Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, cell_expr
                Let last_in_row be row_len minus 1
                If c is less than last_in_row:
                    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, " "
                End If
                Set elem_index to elem_index plus 1
                Set c to c plus 1
            End While
            Set r to r plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, "]"
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Binary expressions re-emit the exact MATLAB operator from the
"matlab_operator" metadata (preserving '^', '.^', '\', matrix-vs-elementwise
spellings) and fall back to mapping the HIR op enum when absent. Operands
are space-padded around the operator.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_binary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, binary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let left be proc hir_get_binary_left from HIR with binary_node
    Let right be proc hir_get_binary_right from HIR with binary_node
    Let left_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, left
    Let right_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, right

    Let op_str be proc metadata_value with binary_node, "matlab_operator"
    If op_str is equal to 0:
        Let hir_op be proc hir_get_binary_op from HIR with binary_node
        Set op_str to proc map_hir_operator_to_matlab with hir_op
    End If

    Let result be proc string_concat from StringPrim with left_expr, " "
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, op_str
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, " "
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, right_expr
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Fallback HIR-op to MATLAB-operator map used only when no preserved spelling
is available. Covers the arithmetic, relational and logical categories the
HIR op enum represents.
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_hir_operator_to_matlab" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_ADD:
        Return "+"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_SUBTRACT:
        Return "-"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY:
        Return "*"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE:
        Return "/"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL:
        Return "=="
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_NOT_EQUAL:
        Return "~="
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_THAN:
        Return "<"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_EQUAL:
        Return "<="
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_THAN:
        Return ">"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_EQUAL:
        Return ">="
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_AND:
        Return "&&"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_OR:
        Return "||"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_AND:
        Return "&"
    End If
    If operator is equal to HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_OR:
        Return "|"
    End If
    Return "+"
End Process

@Reasoning:
A unary expression carrying "matlab_transpose" is a postfix transpose,
re-emitted as "operand'" or "operand.'" from the preserved spelling. Other
unary forms re-emit the preserved prefix operator (~, -, +) before the
operand.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_unary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, unary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operand be proc hir_get_unary_operand from HIR with unary_node
    Let operand_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, operand

    Let transpose be proc metadata_value with unary_node, "matlab_transpose"
    If transpose is not equal to 0:
        Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with operand_expr, transpose
    End If

    Let op_str be proc metadata_value with unary_node, "matlab_operator"
    If op_str is equal to 0:
        Set op_str to "-"
    End If
    Return proc string_concat from StringPrim with op_str, operand_expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Call expressions reconstruct either an anonymous function (when flagged
"matlab_lambda": "@(params) body") or an ordinary "callee(arg, ...)" call.
The callee and each positional argument are rendered recursively.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_call_expression" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_lambda be proc metadata_flag with call_node, "matlab_lambda"
    If is_lambda is equal to 1:
        Return proc generate_lambda with ctx, call_node
    End If

    Let callee be proc hir_get_call_callee from HIR with call_node
    Let callee_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, callee

    Let args_handle be proc hir_get_call_arguments from HIR with call_node
    Let args be proc hir_get_positional_args from HIR with args_handle
    Let arg_count be proc list_length from ListCore with args

    Let result be proc string_concat from StringPrim with callee_expr, "("
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than arg_count:
        Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with args, i
        Let arg_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, arg
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, arg_expr
        Let last be arg_count minus 1
        If i is less than last:
            Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, ", "
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, ")"
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
An anonymous function re-emits "@(params) body" using the joined parameter
names from "matlab_lambda_params" metadata and the single body expression
stored as the call's first positional argument.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_lambda" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let params be proc metadata_value with call_node, "matlab_lambda_params"
    Let result be "@("
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, params
    End If
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, ") "

    Let args_handle be proc hir_get_call_arguments from HIR with call_node
    Let args be proc hir_get_positional_args from HIR with args_handle
    Let arg_count be proc list_length from ListCore with args
    If arg_count is greater than 0:
        Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with args, 0
        Let body_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, body
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, body_expr
    End If
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Index expressions reconstruct MATLAB's three indexing forms from metadata:
dynamic field access "obj.(expr)", a colon range "start:end" /
"start:step:end", cell indexing "base{idx}", or array indexing "base(idx)".
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_index_expression" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let object be proc hir_get_index_object from HIR with index_node
    Let index be proc hir_get_index_value from HIR with index_node

    Let is_dynamic be proc metadata_flag with index_node, "matlab_dynamic_field"
    If is_dynamic is equal to 1:
        Let obj_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, object
        Let field_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, index
        Let dyn be proc string_concat from StringPrim with obj_expr, ".("
        Set dyn to proc string_concat from StringPrim with dyn, field_expr
        Set dyn to proc string_concat from StringPrim with dyn, ")"
        Return dyn
    End If

    Let range_kind be proc metadata_value with index_node, "matlab_range"
    If range_kind is not equal to 0:
        Return proc generate_range with ctx, index_node, range_kind
    End If

    Let object_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, object
    Let index_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, index

    Let is_cell be proc metadata_flag with index_node, "matlab_cell_indexing"
    Let result be object_expr
    If is_cell is equal to 1:
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, "{"
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, index_expr
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, "}"
    Otherwise:
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, "("
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, index_expr
        Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, ")"
    End If
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Re-emits a colon range. A "2" kind is "start:end" (object=start,
index=end). A "3" kind nests an inner "start:step" index inside the object
slot with the outer index being the end value, reconstructed as
"start:step:end".
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_range" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer, range_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_three be proc string_equals from StringCore with range_kind, "3"
    Let object be proc hir_get_index_object from HIR with index_node
    Let end_val be proc hir_get_index_value from HIR with index_node

    If is_three is equal to 1:
        Note: object is the inner "start:step" index expression.
        Let inner_start be proc hir_get_index_object from HIR with object
        Let inner_step be proc hir_get_index_value from HIR with object
        Let start_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, inner_start
        Let step_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, inner_step
        Let end_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, end_val
        Let three be proc string_concat from StringPrim with start_expr, ":"
        Set three to proc string_concat from StringPrim with three, step_expr
        Set three to proc string_concat from StringPrim with three, ":"
        Set three to proc string_concat from StringPrim with three, end_expr
        Return three
    End If

    Let start2 be proc generate_expression with ctx, object
    Let end2 be proc generate_expression with ctx, end_val
    Let two be proc string_concat from StringPrim with start2, ":"
    Set two to proc string_concat from StringPrim with two, end2
    Return two
End Process

@Reasoning:
"obj.field" re-emitted from the HIR member expression's object subtree and
static member name string.
@End Reasoning
Process called "generate_member_expression" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let object be proc hir_get_member_object from HIR with member_node
    Let member_name be proc hir_get_member_name from HIR with member_node
    Let object_expr be proc generate_expression with ctx, object
    Let result be proc string_concat from StringPrim with object_expr, "."
    Set result to proc string_concat from StringPrim with result, member_name
    Return result
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STRING UTILITIES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Splits a string on ", " into a list of substrings. Used to recover the
joined output-parameter / event name lists from metadata. A scan tracks
segment boundaries and slices each piece via string_substring.
@End Reasoning
Process called "split_on_comma_space" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Let parts be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let segment_start be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is equal to 44:
            Let seg_len be i minus segment_start
            Let segment be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, segment_start, seg_len
            proc list_append from ListCore with parts, segment
            Note: skip ", " (comma + space)
            Set i to i plus 2
            Set segment_start to i
        Otherwise:
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    Let tail_len be length minus segment_start
    If tail_len is greater than 0:
        Let tail be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, segment_start, tail_len
        proc list_append from ListCore with parts, tail
    End If
    Return parts
End Process

@Reasoning:
Splits a string on ';' into a list of substrings. Used to recover the
per-row element counts from matrix metadata.
@End Reasoning
Process called "split_on_semicolon" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Let parts be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let segment_start be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is equal to 59:
            Let seg_len be i minus segment_start
            Let segment be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, segment_start, seg_len
            proc list_append from ListCore with parts, segment
            Set i to i plus 1
            Set segment_start to i
        Otherwise:
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    Let tail_len be length minus segment_start
    If tail_len is greater than 0:
        Let tail be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, segment_start, tail_len
        proc list_append from ListCore with parts, tail
    End If
    Return parts
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a non-negative decimal string into an integer by accumulating each
digit. Used to read the per-row element counts back from matrix metadata.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_decimal" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let value be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
            If ch is less than or equal to 57:
                Let digit be ch minus 48
                Set value to value multiplied by 10
                Set value to value plus digit
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return value
End Process
